Kennesaw Mountain National Battlefield Park was authorized as a unit of the National Park System on
			 June 26, 1935, prior to which year, parts of  the Park had been acquired
			 and protected by Civil  War veterans and the War Department;

Kennesaw Mountain National Battlefield Park protects Kennesaw Mountain and Kolb’s  Farm, which are
			 battle sites along the route of General Sherman’s 1864 campaign to take
			 Atlanta;
